<TEXT>
a 4 million lawsuit claiming sexual 
harassment and discrimination was filed thursday against john j 
mclaughlin the talk show host and washington editor of national 
review magazine 
the plaintiff linda d dean 35 of alexandria va was 
executive assistant at mclaughlins oliver productions which 
produces his syndicated talk show the mclaughlin group from 
december 1987 until april 15 of this year 
the us district court suit alleged that mclaughlin fired her 
from her 35000ayear job in retaliation for her protests of 
sex discrimination and sexual harassment toward herself and other 
women who worked in the office 
mclaughlin 60 has been married since 1975 to labor secretary 
ann dore mclaughlin 
deans suit seeks 1 million in compensatory damages from 
mclaughlin and oliver productions jointly and 15 million in 
punitive damages from each defendant 
mclaughlins attorney former white house counsel fred fielding 
said in a statement john mclaughlin and oliver productions 
emphatically deny these bizarre and outrageous allegations and 
will seek swift disposition of this matter through the judicial 
system we will have no further public comment on these allegations 
or on the possible motivations of the plaintiff until that time 
</TEXT>
