shipping executives said the captain said a few bullets pierced 
the ship but caused no injuries 
earlier reports from irans official islamic republic news 
agency said 1031 civilians were injured in an iraqi chemical bomb 
attack tuesday in the town of oshnaviyeh in the northern province 
of west azerbaijan 
today irna raised the injury toll to 1700 
over 100 of the victims mainly women and children have 
reportedly been seriously affected and are being treated in various 
hospitals in the province irna said 
iraq denied it dropped chemical bombs on the area according to 
the official iraqi news agency 
on wednesday iranian foreign minister ali akbar velayati lodged 
a formal protest with the security council over the alleged 
chemical attack and said it should impose sanctions on iraq 
a report released monday by a un team concluded that iraq has 
made repeated and extensive use of chemical warfare in the war 
