<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880804-0066 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
raising levels of socalled good cholesterol 
and lowering levels of bad cholesterol in men with elevated 
cholesterol levels lowered their risk of coronary heart disease 
says a study released thursday 
the findings followed up a fiveyear experiment by the helsinki 
heart study in which a drug called gemfibrozil was used to raise 
the level of highdensity lipoprotein hdl cholesterol the good 
cholesterol and lower damaging lowdensity cholesterol ldl in 
a group of 2051 men 40 to 45 years old with elevated levels of 
cholesterol other than hdl 
the initial report of the experiment published in november 
showed the group who took the drug suffered 34 percent fewer heart 
attacks than 2030 other men who were given placebos over the same 
period 
the followup study emphasizes the role of hdl in lowering heart 
disease risks and will change the way doctors measure cholesterol 
levels said dr vesa maaninen of helsinki university 
there was a twofour percent drop in numbers of cardiac 
arrests with every one percent increase in hdl cholesterol said 
maaninen 
many studies have shown previously that there is a statistical 
link between high levels of hdl low levels of ldl and a reduced 
likelihood of coronary heart disease in which waxy buildups in 
the coronary arteries slow and ultimately prevent the flow of blood 
to the heart muscle 
barry lewis a british pathologist at londons st thomas 
hospital said that on average nearly twothirds of people in 
industrialized nations have high ldl cholesterol 
he said that while most people can lower ldl cholesterol levels 
and raise hdl levels with a change of diet some have persistently 
high levels and would benefit most from medication 
maaninen came to london to report these latest findings being 
published this week in the journal of the american medical 
association 
maaninen said the drug produced little difference in the rate of 
cardiac arrests in the first two years but that after that the 
rate decreased the longer the men took the drug 
marshall molloy a spokesman for the manufacturers 
warnerlambert co said gemfibrozil has been approved temporarily 
