consensus that believed it was america and only america that 
could lead the world to freedom and peace 
his positions amount to a rejection of americas role as a 
world leader and a repudiation of the truman doctrine and the 
vision of john kennedy bush said 
his speech came in the wake of the vice presidents repeated 
attempts this week to portray dukakis as soft on foreign policy 
an area seen by republican strategists as one in which the 
massachusetts governor is vulnerable 
bush cited dukakis support for a nuclear freeze and opposition 
to a new mx missile the midgetman missile and the reagan 
administrations proposed star wars nuclear defense system 
dukakis campaigning in mississippi was asked by reporters if 
he still supports a nuclear weapons freeze sure and a 
comprehensive test ban treaty he said 
later aboard his campaign plane dukakis said he originally 
supported a nuclear freeze because we wanted to stop the 
administration from expanding the arsenal 
now its turned around and were talking about reduction im 
for reductions now he said there are certain weapons systems 
whose development i favor but there are also serious 
negotiations under way im for developing certain weapons systems 
and for substantially reducing others 
asked again if he was for a freeze dukakis said no i favor 
the development of certain arms systems i favor deep cuts in 
strategic weapons systems 
bush said dukakis views add up to no modernization of us 
forces and no modernization amounts to unilateral disarmament 
dukakis called bushs disarmament charge nonsense and 
added we have a massive survivable nuclear deterrent right now 
12000 strategic nuclear warheads what we dont have is the kind 
of strong conventional defense capability we must have and that is 
going to be my top priority as president 
bush said the democratic platform is no help in trying to 
determine where the democratic presidential nominee stood on 
foreign policy issues 
the democratic platform is the black hole of american 
politics he said issues get sucked into it and lost never to 
reappear again 
at an airport news conference bush was asked whether members of 
his campaign staff had been advancing rumors concerning dukakis 
mental health 
i assume no one in my campaign is doing anything of that 
kind he said i would thoroughly disapprove of it 
he also said president reagan was broadminded in retracting 
