<TEXT>
st basils cathedral the 400yearold patchwork 
of color anchoring one end of red square has serious structural 
defects but is kept open because of the money it earns from 
tourism a newspaper said thursday 
sovietskaya kultura said st basils built in 15541560 by 
order of ivan the terrible has cracked walls a leaky basement and 
problems caused by temperature variations and moisture 
its onion domes of red green gold and blue sit atop a central 
chapel and nine small ones connected by narrow passageways 
more than 300000 tourists a year visit the cathedral one of 
the most famous attractions in the soviet union the paper said 
the structure is an adjunct of the state historical museum 
tourists let in heat cold or moisture depending on the season 
and officials discovered five years ago the basement was absorbing 
underground water a terrible loss that has victimized many of 
moscows monuments of architecture the paper said 
instead of closing the church for repairs or on days when it is 
too hot too cold or too humid officials keep it open for the 
tourists sovietskaya kultura reported 
the main thing is that the cathedral brings without 
interruption about 300000 rubles roughly 480 million of clear 
income every year to the state historical museum it said 
the museum itself on the opposite side red square has been 
closed for the two years for repairs and probably will stay closed 
for two more the newspaper said that leaves st basils and a 
small museum at moscows novodevichy cemetery as the state 
historicals only moneymakers 
to close the cathedral in this situation means leaving workers 
of the state historical museum without an income it said 
sovietskaya kultura paper said it did not want to sensationalize 
the cathdrals problems but warned that many architectural 
landmarks have been damaged because cursory inspections did not 
reveal their true structural problems 
it said there is no tragedy so far whether one will happen 
no one knows but we have to know if some misfortune befalls 
the cathedral our entire generation will never be cleansed of the 
shame 
ivan the terrible ordered the cathedral built to celebrate the 
russian defeat of tatar invaders at kazan 
legend says he had the architects blinded after st basils was 
built so they could not design anything to rival it 
