un secretarygeneral javier perez de 
cuellar said thursday that both iran and iraq accept the concept of 
facetoface peace talks and the big question is when will they 
take place 
the issue of direct negotiations before a ceasefire has created 
an impasse in talks aimed at ending the 8yearold persian gulf 
war iraq had demanded facetoface talks before a ceasefire iran 
said they can only take place afterward 
the concept of direct talks is accepted by both sides and the 
matter is when perez de cuellar told reporters thursday as he 
left un headquarters that is something on which i am working 
diplomatic sources speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
un chief proposed to both sides that he announce a ceasefire 
date and simultaneously invite both iran and iraq to hold direct 
talks on a comprehensive peace treaty 
