<TEXT>
bond prices were higher in mostly quiet trading 
early today as the market awaited fridays government report on 
the nations unemployment in july 
the treasurys closely watched 30year bond was up point or 
375 for every 1000 in face value by midday its yield which 
moves inversely to its price and is often an indicator of interest 
rate trends fell to 904 percent from 906 percent late wednesday 
analysts said bond prices were lifted on a wave of buying early 
in the trading session 
we had a big flurry for the first 10 minutes and weve been 
asleep ever since said jay goldinger a principal of capital 
insight inc an investment firm in beverly hills calif 
many investors were caught short after selling bonds wednesday 
on speculation that the jobless report for july would show a strong 
growth in the number of employed analysts said 
higher employment tends to depress bond prices because it 
implies a stronger economy rising wages greater demand for credit 
and inflation which erodes the value of fixedincome securities 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
government issues edged up 132 point to 116 point intermediate 
maturities rose 116 point to 532 point and 20year issues gained 
516 point according to data provided by telerate inc a 
financial information service 
the movement of a point equals a change of 10 in the price of a 
bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer was up 159 at 114305 
in corporate trading industrial bonds rose moodys investment 
grade corporate bond index which measures price movements on 80 
corporate bonds with maturities of five years or longer edged up 
071 to 28504 
threemonth treasury bills meanwhile slipped 1 basis point to 
a discounted rate of 686 percent and a yield of 707 percent 
sixmonth bills declined 2 basis points to a discounted rate of 
707 percent and a yield of 742 percent while oneyear bills were 
down 1 basis point at 729 percent to yield 781 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
